data_variables.name: df
data_variables.description: DataFrame variable used for most plotting functions. It contains the processed data to analyze.

data_variables.name: nHistogramShown
data_variables.description: Parameter for the number of histograms to display.

data_variables.name: nHistogramPerRow
data_variables.description: Parameter for the number of histograms to display per row.

data_variables.name: graphWidth
data_variables.description: Parameter specifying the width of the correlation matrix plot.

data_variables.name: plotSize
data_variables.description: Parameter specifying the size of scatter plots.

data_variables.name: textSize
data_variables.description: Parameter for the size of text annotations in scatter plots.

data_flow.created: Not explicitly shown in notebook; implies it's created when data is read from a source.
